pull_request.title: Bump cryptography from 37.0.4 to 38.0.3
pull_request.body:
Bumps [cryptography](https://github.com/pyca/cryptography) from 37.0.4 to 38.0.3.
Changelog

Sourced from cryptography's changelog.

38.0.3 - 2022-11-01


* Updated Windows, macOS, and Linux wheels to be compiled with OpenSSL 3.0.7,
  which resolves *CVE-2022-3602* and *CVE-2022-3786*.

.. _v38-0-2:


38.0.2 - 2022-10-11 (YANKED)

.. attention::

This release was subsequently yanked from PyPI due to a regression in OpenSSL.
  • Updated Windows, macOS, and Linux wheels to be compiled with OpenSSL 3.0.6.

.. _v38-0-1:

38.0.1 - 2022-09-07


* Fixed parsing TLVs in ASN.1 with length greater than 65535 bytes (typically
  seen in large CRLs).

.. _v38-0-0:


38.0.0 - 2022-09-06

  • Final deprecation of OpenSSL 1.1.0. The next release of cryptography will drop support.
  • We no longer ship manylinux2010 wheels. Users should upgrade to the latest pip to ensure this doesn't cause issues downloading wheels on their platform. We now ship manylinux_2_28 wheels for users on new enough platforms.
  • Updated the minimum supported Rust version (MSRV) to 1.48.0, from 1.41.0. Users with the latest pip will typically get a wheel and not need Rust installed, but check :doc:/installation for documentation on installing a newer rustc if required.
  • :meth:~cryptography.fernet.Fernet.decrypt and related methods now accept both str and bytes tokens.
  • Parsing CertificateSigningRequest restores the behavior of enforcing that the Extension critical field must be correctly encoded DER. See the issue <https://github.com/pyca/cryptography/issues/6368>_ for complete details.
  • Added two new OpenSSL functions to the bindings to support an upcoming pyOpenSSL release.
  • When parsing :class:~cryptography.x509.CertificateRevocationList and

... (truncated)

  • 7d9c6c3 Bump for 38.0.3 release (#7761)
  • 39f8011 attempt to workaround downstream package testing situation (#7725) (#7757)
  • 5b12ac8 Use PyPy binaries from manylinux image instead of our own (#7678) (#7693)
  • 277ee0d 38.0.2 release (#7691)
  • ce119b8 version properly in the changelog (#7578)
  • 3ff5218 Backport tlv fix, 38.0.1 bump (#7576)
  • 52d6f1a version bump for 38 release (#7567)

repo.description: Python helpers to integrate with Shinkansen

commits.message: Update dependencies
Ignore any sqlite db
Refactor base url construction

Add a simplistic tester module

It allows us to quickly (stress) test the network (and payout
operators) to check if everything is working as expected.
Remove unused method
Better error handling when sending payout messages
Ignore local dev env script

Refactor code into separate files

So we can make it easier to read
Document the SHINKANSEN_API_HOST in README
Fix references to logging -> app.logger
Add option to specify a sender email
Fix warning about max amount in new payout form

Allow to set a max amount for payouts

So we can help a partner with final checks on prod without moving
significant amounts of money

Handle Shinkansen's messages

We now update the payout status and response contents when Shinkansen
calls us back.

payload.description: Python helpers to integrate with Shinkansen

commits.message: Bump version to 0.6.0
Add verification of incoming responses

Add support for responses (only payouts for now)

Now we can parse responses for payouts. It's written in an extensible
way so we support responses for other transactions (such as those
related to certificates)
Add dummy endpoint to receive shinkansen messages

Change deploy command to include both tamagotchis

(A partner bank wanted their own testing toy)

Rearrange env variables in README

So the required ones appear first
Add default legal name to README
Update python-shinkansen to 0.5.2

payload.description: Python helpers to integrate with Shinkansen

commits.message: Bump version to 0.5.2
Handle 400 error code without json body

Add more customization via env vars

Now you can set the sender's legal name. Also useful for end-to-end
testing.

Add more env vars to customize sender details.

We now allow to set a custom RUT (CLID) and a custom account number.
This is useful to use tamagotchi for end-to-end tests with arbitrary
credentials.

Update jwcrypto and python-shinkansen

So we stop depending on a vulnerable jwcrypto (even though we are not
affected by the vulnerability)

payload.description: Python helpers to integrate with Shinkansen

commits.message:
Update to jwcrypto 1.4.x

1.3.x has a security vulnerability which doesn't impact our usage.

That said, it's better to not depend on vulnerable libs.
Bump version to 0.5.1

Avoid trailing slash in API base_url

It doesn't break anything, but still better to avoid double slashes.

Allow to change the sender in messages.

This way this codebase can be used to test signatures or certificates
for participants different to tamagotchi itself.
Rename README to reflect we use markdown format
More tweaking to the stress tester

Update jwcrypto and python-shinkansen

So we stop depending on a vulnerable jwcrypto (even though we are not
affected by the vulnerability)

payload.description: Python helpers to integrate with Shinkansen

commits.message:
Update to jwcrypto 1.4.x

1.3.x has a security vulnerability which doesn't impact our usage.

That said, it's better to not depend on vulnerable libs.
Bump version to 0.5.1

Avoid trailing slash in API base_url

It doesn't break anything, but still better to avoid double slashes.

Allow to change the sender in messages.

This way this codebase can be used to test signatures or certificates
for participants different to tamagotchi itself.
Rename README to reflect we use markdown format
